# Data Structures: Heaps

<span class="lead"> </span>

Heaps Module

## [Heaps](../module/recNbOiLfM7bfQ0aE)

Heaps are a type of tree where the highest, or lowest, values “float” to the top. We’ll examine how to construct one and discuss some of their uses.

#### Objectives:

-   Student should be able to enumerate how heaps work as well as what some of their pros and cons are.
